Source: Art Album NZ Flora
Author: FEATON
Vol / Page: 141-142
Edition:
Quote: DROSERA. (<i>Linn.</i>) The Sundew ... one can scarcely examine a plant without finding the wings and legs of insects, on one or more of the leaves. ... This extremely interesting genus is represented in New Zealand by six species, all of which are said to digest meats, and are known to [142] the settlers as `Fly-catchers'.
