Date: 0/9/2001
Source: NZ Geographic
Author:
Vol / Page: No. 53/47
Edition:
Quote: [Caption] Sundews (<i>Drosera</i>,..) are tiny carnivorous plants found in boggy ground. Sticky droplets on the hairy red leaves ensnare small insects, which the plant consumes using its enzymes... One often sees the carcasses of small insects caught in their leaves - a grim clue as to how these plants get their nitrogen and phosphorus.
